merge, remix, publish, and distribute the Project, including for creating
your own games or builds based on it, subject to the following condition:

You must give reasonable credit to the original author, qtepi, by doing
at least one of the following:

(a) Keep this licence file included with the Project files, and include a
link to the original GitHub repository:
https://github.com/riceareseeds/qtepi-s-experimental-cars; or

(b) Credit "qtepi" somewhere a player or visitor would naturally see it —
for example, in the game's description, an in-game credits/about
area, or a loading/menu screen. A link to the GitHub repository above
is a bonus here, but not required — the credit itself is what
matters; or

(c) If the Project (or your remix or build of it) is used as a Polytoria
world, place credit for "qtepi" in that world's description.
~~~
If you share or post about your remix or build elsewhere (such as a
forum post, social media, or video), you don't need to repeat the
credit there if the post includes a link that leads people to where
the credit is already visible (e.g. a link to the world itself, or to
the GitHub repository above). If the post doesn't include such a
link, then credit "qtepi" directly in the post.
~~~
You only need to satisfy one of (a), (b), or (c) — not all three. The goal
is simply that people encountering your version can find out the original
was made by qtepi, and can easily find the original GitHub project if they
want to — it doesn't need to be prominent or formal.

